🔹 1. SSL/TLS (Secure Communication)
------------------------------
 - Secure communication between client & server
 
 SSL → Old (deprecated) : Secure Socket Layer
 TLS → Modern (used now) : Transport Layer security

 Used in:
 - HTTPS
 - APIs
 - Web apps

 Example:
 http://site.com  → Not secure
 https://site.com → Secure

 TLS Flow:
 Client → Hello
 Server → Certificate
 Client → Verify → Encrypted communication starts

 Features:
 - Encryption → Data hidden (Unreadable)
 - Integrity → No tampering (Not modified)
 - Authentication → Verify server (Identity)


🔹 2. IPSec (Network Security)
------------------------------
 - Secures communication between networks or system
 - A protocol suite that secures IP-Level communication

 Used in:
 - VPN
 - Site-to-site connection
 - Cloud networking

 Modes:
 Transport Mode → Encrypts data only (Host to Host)
 Tunnel Mode → Encrypts entire packet (Its used in VPN)

 Difference:
 TLS → Secure message - Looking a message inside an envelope
   
 IPSec → Secure network - Securing the entire road between cities

Scenario :
  1) Secure Website : TSL-https
  2) Connect Office to AWS VPC : IPSec - VPN
  3) API Security : TSL - measures encrypted data
  4) Hyprid Cloud : IPSec - Cloud 

