🔹 5. Shell Scripting
------------------------------
 - Writing a sequence of Linux commands in a file to Automate tasks
 - Automating Linux commands

 Shell:
 - Program that executes commands on the system

 Types:
 - Bash (most used)
 - sh
 - zsh

 Example : sudo apt update 
           sudo apt install nginx -y
    Automate:
        #!/bin/bash
        sudo apt update
        sudo apt install nginx -y

🔹 6. Basic Script
------------------------------
 #!/bin/bash          ------------> Shebang : Tells system to use Bash # comment 
 echo "Hello World"   ------------> echo prints output

 Commands:
 chmod +x script.sh
./script.sh

Shell vs sh vs bash
-------------------
-> Shell = category (not a specific tool)

-> sh = Bourne shell One of the oldest Unix shells
   * Basic and minimal
   Features: 
      • Simple scripting 
      • Limited functionality 

-> Bash = bourne again shell 
    * Improved version of sh 
    * Default shell in most linux systems 
    Features:
      • Variables 
      • Arrays 
      • Loops 
      • Advanced Scripting 
      • Auto-completion 


# How to check a current shell?
